Limpopo police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe said police are following leads on 18 suspects that bombed an ATM in Twin City shopping complex Burgersfort on Friday. We have launched a manhunt for 18 heavily armed suspects who bombed an ATM in Burgersfort. The suspects bombed two ATMs and made off with an undisclosed amount of cash, Ngoepe said.He added that one of the three vehicles used in the crime was recovered some distance away from the scene.It is alleged that the suspects instructed security officials to lie down before shooting randomly and killing one guard.The police are still investigating the matter and no arrest have yet been made.-TNA Reporter